Snake Game
This is a classic Snake Game implemented in Python using the Pygame library. The game provides a simple and interactive interface where the player controls a snake and tries to eat food while avoiding collisions with the boundaries of the game window and the snake's own tail.

Snake Game

Features
Simple and intuitive gameplay
Smooth controls using arrow keys
Randomly generated food for the snake to eat
Increasing snake length as it eats food
Game over when the snake collides with boundaries or its own tail
Score tracking to keep a record of the player's performance
Installation
To run the Snake Game locally on your machine, follow these steps:

Ensure you have Python 3.x installed on your system. If not, you can download and install Python from the official Python website: python.org.

Clone this repository or download the source code as a ZIP file and extract it to your desired location.

